The paper deals with the problem of simultaneously learning a k-means clustering and deep feature representation from unlabelled data. This falls under the domain of machine learning and specifically, unsupervised learning. The paper proposes a novel method for deep clustering using concrete k-means, which involves developing a gradient estimator for the non-differentiable k-means objective via the Gumbel-Softmax reparameterisation trick. This suggests that the paper could be classified under several sub-categories of computer science, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
